hh3cCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Classifier configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSClassifierIndex.description: Index of Traffic Classifier. Begin with 0.

hh3cCBQoSClassifierOperator.name: hh3cCBQoSClassifierOperator
hh3cCBQoSClassifierOperator.description: Operator of the match rules of traffic classifier. Software QoS supports and, or. Hardware QoS supports and.

hh3cCBQoSClassifierLayer.name: hh3cCBQoSClassifierLayer
hh3cCBQoSClassifierLayer.description: Configuration layer of traffic classifier. Only hardware QoS support it. 1(unavailable) is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 1(unavailable) can't be set.

hh3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex.name: hh3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex
hh3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIndex when creating rows in the hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable. Begin with 0. If the value of this node is 65535, it indicates creating a row in hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable is not permitted.

hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Match Rule configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot
hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.description: Whether the if-match rule is a match or matchNot statement. Software QoS supports match, matchNot. Hardware QoS supports match.

hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue
hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.description: Value of Match Rule. SourceMAC: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match source-mac 0101-0202-0303' DestinationMAC: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match destination-mac 0101-0202-0303' Classifier: SIZE (1..31) classifier name InboundInterface: SIZE (1..47) interface description TopMostVlanID, VlanID:SIZE(1..39), up to 8 value can be input; for example: 1#11#111#1111 means the match rule if 'if-match vlanid 1 11 111 1111' SourceIp: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match source-ip mac-address 0101-0202-0303' other types: Set is not permitted. Zero-length String will be returned when getting.

hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1
hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.description: Value of Match Rule. IPv4 ACL: 2000~5999 IPv6 ACL: 2000~3999; 10000~42767 Software QoS: 2000~3999 Hardware Qos: 10000~42767 RtpPort: start-port: 2000~65535 IpPrec: value: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match ip-prec 0 1 4 6' Dscp: value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. for example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 32 33 63' Vlan8021p: value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match customer-dot1p 0 1 4 6' MplsExp: value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the 8 value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match mpls 0 1 4 6' SourceIp: 1~4095 QosLocalID: 1~4095 AtmClp: 0~1 FrDe: 0~1 LocalPrecedence: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match localprecedence 0 1 4 6' DropPriority: 0~2, up to 3 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 3 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~2. ServiceDot1p: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match service-dot1p 0 1 4 6' other types: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2
hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.description: Value of Match Rule. RtpPort(3): end-port: 2000~65535 Dscp(6): value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of hh3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. for example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 0 1 31' other types: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType
hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType.description: A value that represents a type of Internet address. unknown(0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address which is not in one of the formats defined below. ipv4(1) An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention. ipv6(2) A global IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention. ipv4z(3) A non-global IPv4 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z textual convention. ipv6z(4) A non-global IPv6 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z textual convention. dns(16) A DNS domain name as defined by the InetAddressDNS textual convention. Value of match rule. SourceIp support this node. other types: Set is not permitted. Unknown will be returned when getting.

hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress.name: hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress
hh3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress.description: Denotes a generic Internet address. SourceIP support this node. other types: Set is not permitted. NULL will be returned when getting.

hh3cCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Behavior configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of CAR feature configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSCarEbs.name: hh3cCBQoSCarEbs
hh3cCBQoSCarEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only software QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarPir.name: hh3cCBQoSCarPir
hh3cCBQoSCarPir.description: Peak Information Rate. Unit: kbps. Only hardware QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarPbs.name: hh3cCBQoSCarPbs
hh3cCBQoSCarPbs.description: Peak Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only hardware QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarGreenAction.name: hh3cCBQoSCarGreenAction
hh3cCBQoSCarGreenAction.description: Green Action Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

hh3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.name: hh3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue
hh3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When green action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass,discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarYellowAction.name: hh3cCBQoSCarYellowAction
hh3cCBQoSCarYellowAction.description: Yellow Action: Only hardware QoS support this node. Hardware QoS support pass, discard, remark. invalid is returned only when getting value from software QoS. invalid can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.name: hh3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue
hh3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSCarRedAction.name: hh3cCBQoSCarRedAction
hh3cCBQoSCarRedAction.description: Red Action: Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

hh3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.name: hh3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue
hh3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of aggregative CAR applied CBQ feature configuration information. Aggregative CAR is managed by HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB. So, you can use HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB to get some details information about aggregative CAR.

hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry.name: hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry
hh3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry.description: Aggregative CAR feature applied CBQ configuration information entry.

hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex.name: hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex
hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex.description: Index of aggregative CAR. It is equal to hh3cIfQoSAggregativeCarIndex at HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName.name: hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName
hh3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName.description: Name of aggregative CAR. It is equal to hh3cIfQoSAggregativeCarName at HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

hh3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.description: A table of GTS feature configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSGtsCbs.name: hh3cCBQoSGtsCbs
hh3cCBQoSGtsCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte default: max(cir*1/2,15000)

hh3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Remarking feature configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSRemarkValue.name: hh3cCBQoSRemarkValue
hh3cCBQoSRemarkValue.description: Value to remark: for IpPrecedence: 0~7 for Dscp: 0~63 for MplsExp: 0~7 for Vlan8021p: 0~7 for AtmClp: 0~1 for FrDe: 0~1 for VlanID: 1~4094 for QosLocalID: 1~4095 for DropPrecedence: 0~2 for LocalPrecedence: 0~7 for TopMostVlanID: 1~4094

hh3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.description: A table of queue feature configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSQueueDropType.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueDropType
hh3cCBQoSQueueDropType.description: The drop type of queue. Only valid for AF and WFQ queue. typeUnavailable is returned only when getting value about EF queue. typeUnavailable can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueLength.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueLength
hh3cCBQoSQueueLength.description: The length of QueueLength. Only valid for tail-drop type of AF and WFQ queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about EF queue or WRED type of AF and WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit
hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.description: Bandwidth Unit: Absolute, Unit Kbps (1) Percent, Unit % (2) Only valid for EF and AF queue. 0 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. 0 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue
hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.description: Bandwidth value: Absolute value: 8~10000000. Unit: Kbps Percent value: 1~100. Only valid for EF and AF queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueCbs.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueCbs
hh3cCBQoSQueueCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only valid for EF queue. Default: If the value of 'hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is between 1500 and 2000000, the default value of this object is 'hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25';If the value of 'hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is larger than or equal to 2000000, the default value of this object is 2000000; If the value of 'hh3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is less than or equal to 1500, the default value of this object is 1500. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber
hh3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.description: Max number of hashed queues (a power of 2). Only valid for WFQ. 'unavailable' is returned only when getting value about AF or EF queue. 'unavailable' can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.name: hh3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio
hh3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.description: Committed Burst Size Ratio. CBS = CBS_Ratio * Bandwidth(k bps) Only valid for EF queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

hh3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSWredWeightConst.name: hh3cCBQoSWredWeightConst
hh3cCBQoSWredWeightConst.description: Specify weight for calculating mean queue depth.

hh3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSWredClassValue.name: hh3cCBQoSWredClassValue
hh3cCBQoSWredClassValue.description: The class value. For IP precedence based WRED, the class is IP precedence, and range is 0~7. For DSCP based WRED, the class is DSCP, and range is 0~63.

hh3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.name: hh3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit
hh3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.description: The low limit of queue depth.

hh3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.name: hh3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit
hh3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.description: The high limit of queue depth.

hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Policy Routing configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.name: hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop
hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.description: The next-hop ip address for redirection.

hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.name: hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup
hh3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.description: Whether forward the packet according to the routing table When the next-hop IP address for redirection is not valid. Backup means forwarding. NoBackup means not forwarding.

hh3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Nat configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.description: A table of firewall configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.description: A table of sampling configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable.description: A table of account configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.description: A table of redirect configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.description: ifIndex. Only the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectType is interface, can be set this node.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType.description: A value that represents a type of Internet address. unknown(0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address which is not in one of the formats defined below. ipv4(1) An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention. ipv6(2) A global IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention. ipv4z(3) A non-global IPv4 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z textual convention. ipv6z(4) A non-global IPv6 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z textual convention. dns(16) A DNS domain name as defined by the InetAddressDNS textual convention. Now supports ipv4 and ipv6. Only the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectType is next-hop, can be set this node and hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1 or hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1.description: IP Address. If the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectType is not next-hop, Zero-length String will be returned when getting. If the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6, this node is set necessarily.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.description: IP Address. If the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectType is not next-hop, Zero-length String will be returned when getting. If the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6, this node is set optionally.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1.description: IfIndex for ipv6 next hop . If and only if the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6 and hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1 is set, this node can be set.

hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2.name: hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2
hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2.description: IfIndex for ipv6 next hop . If and only if the value of hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6 and hh3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2 is set, this node can be set.

hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable.description: A table of priority map configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex.name: hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex
hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex.description: Index of map group. Map group is managed by HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName.name: hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName
hh3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName.description: Name of map group. Map group is managed by HH3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

hh3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of flow mirror configuration information.

hh3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex.name: hh3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex
hh3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex.description: IfIndex of destination interface. Only the value of hh3cCBQoSMirrorType is interface, can be set this node. For example: 1#11#111#1111 means the flow mirror destination ifindex is 1,11,111 and 1111. '#' is list separator for all IfIndex value.

hh3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID.name: hh3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID
hh3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID.description: Destination vlan of flow mirror, Only the value of hh3cCBQoSMirrorType is vlan, can be set this node.

hh3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable
hh3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable.description: Insert a service VLAN tag or customer VLAN tag into a packet. A VLAN tag contains the VLAN ID field and the 802.1p priority field. Both the service VLAN ID and the customer VLAN ID can not be set at the same time. One of them must be set.
